    <div class="flat flat-intro">
      <div class="intro">
        <p>
          Total quality management (TQM) consists of organisation-wide efforts
          to install and make permanent a climate in which an organisation
          continuously improves its ability to deliver high-quality products and
          services to customers. While there is no widely agreed-upon approach,
          TQM efforts typically draw heavily on the previously developed tools
          and techniques of quality control.
        </p>

        <p>
          This document is meant to introduce the concept of TQM and all
          submodules that it encapsulates. It is also meant as a reference for
          TQM teaching. This document is split into sections which each cover a
          core aspect of TQM. At the end of the document is a quiz that should
          be used to test your understanding of TQM.
        </p>

        <p>
          What follows is a video that introduces TQM in the context of a
          sandwich production line.
        </p>

        <p>&nbsp;</p>

        <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/wSskmZpqsIM"></iframe>
      </div>
